			<h3>Working in Fullscreen mode</h3>
			<p class="intro">We all know how having that extra bit of real estate can really help your productivity, so we decided to add a feature to Configurator to allow you to easily toggle between fullscreen mode and normal mode.</p>
			<h4>Clicking the fullscreen link in the top shelf:</h4>
			<p><img src="../administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-fullscreen-bg.png" alt="maskot" border="0" align="right" style="margin:-35px -7px 0 15px" />There are two ways that you can use this feature. The first is by using the "Fullscreen mode" link in the top shelf (see the pic below), which </p>
			<h4>Using the built in shortcuts:</h4>
			<p>The other (and easier) way is to use the built in keyboard shortcuts. If you are on a mac, simply pressing <strong>cmd + f</strong> to toggle between the two views. All other users (windows, linux, etc) can use <strong>ctrl + f</strong>.</p>
